The four right angles add up to $4 * 90^{\circ} = 360^{\circ}$, so $\theta$ must be $817^{\circ} - 360^{\circ} = 457^{\circ}$.
However, since a full rotation is $360^{\circ}$, the equivalent angle less than $360^{\circ}$ is $457^{\circ} - 360^{\circ} = \boxed{\text{(D) }97^{\circ}}$.

