\begin{align*}
24^2 \cdot s^2 &= 0.64 \cdot (24s + 25d)^2 \\
&= 0.64 \cdot (576s^2 + 2 \cdot 24 \cdot 25sd + 25^2d^2) \\
&= 368.64s^2 + 768d \cdot s + 100d^2 \\
576s^2 &= 368.64s^2 + 768d \cdot s + 100d^2 \\
207.36s^2 &= 768d \cdot s + 100d^2 \\
\frac{207.36s^2}{s^2} &= \frac{768d \cdot s}{s^2} + \frac{100d^2}{s^2} \\
207.36 &= 768d + 100 \left(\frac{d}{s}\right) \\
107.36 &= 768 \left(\frac{d}{s}\right).
\end{align*}

Therefore, the ratio $\frac{d}{s} = \frac{107.36}{768} = \boxed{\frac{7}{16}}$.



