Since $\overline{AB} \| \overline{CD}$, we have $\angle BAO=\angle ADO=\theta$, say. Then by the inscribed angle theorem, $\angle BDO=2 \theta$. However, since $\triangle BOD$ is a right triangle, $\angle BDO=90^\circ$, so $\theta=45^\circ$. Since angle $\theta$ cuts off arc $\overline{AB}$, $m\widehat{AB}=45^\circ$. But since in degrees measure $360^\circ$ corresponds to $2\pi$ inches, $1^\circ$ corresponds to $\dfrac{2\pi}{360} = \dfrac{1}{180} \pi$ inches. Thus, $m\widehat{AB}=45\left(\dfrac{1}{180} \pi\right)=\dfrac{1}{4}\pi$. Thus, since $AD=36$ inches is the diameter, the length of $\widehat{AB}$ is $\dfrac{1}{4}\pi \cdot AD = \boxed{9\pi}$ inches.

